The paper deals with capacity in a network, which is a topic commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT). The addition of a single bit of communication also suggests a focus on network communication (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of the term "memoryless network" suggests a possible connection to distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the study of capacity regions in networks can also be relevant to computer communication (cs.CC).
